message:
Hi Stephen,
 thanks for all your work and time you spend, I've learned a lot.

My question is: When I have multiple nested functions and the inner function has an <code>await DownloadFileAsync();</code>
Do I need to have async/await all the way up the call stack? Because sometimes this didn't work, e.g. when the outer function is a Constructor:

```cs
public Constructor()  // async doesn't work here
{  
  await Function1();
}
public async Task Function1()
{
  await Function2(); // I would prefer to stop the async/await here
  // use _globalVar here
}
public async Task Function2()
{
  var _globalVar = await DownloadFileAsync();
}
```

How can I do this? (perhaps with WaitAll/WhenAll?)

Thanks & regards Thomas
